    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 11 March 1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He has just received Oláh’s letters. Francesco II Sforza
                            thanks him for the thorough report. They have heard that the Anabaptist
                            plague is spreading in Antwerp. King Frederick II is marrying Dorothea
                            of Denmark. The Emperor is planning to go to Italy, and Andrea Doria is
                            about to set out for Baradino at his order. The Pope tends to side with
                            the French, but this does not matter. The prince has written to the
                            Queen in detail about what they have heard about Hayreddin Barbarossa
                            Pasha, and the events that have taken place in Rome and Spain. The
                            Italian sword Oláh is getting is, simply put, a masterpiece.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao suo salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Quae XXI. item XXII. praeteriti exarasti, pridie accepi.<note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.1">We do not know these
                        letters.</note><persName>Princeps</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.2">Francesco II Sforza.</note> meus tibi gratias agit, quod tam
                    diligenter operam tuam in scriptione praestes et te rogat, ut in ea assidue
                    verseris. Audivimus Antverpienses laborare pestilentia Anabaptistica; si verum
                    est, fac, ut sciam. Dux <persName>Fridericus</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">Frederick II, Elector Palatine of the Rhine.</note> uxorem
                    ducet illustrissimam <persName>Dorotheam</persName>,<note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">Dorothea of Denmark married Frederick II, Elector Palatine
                        of the Rhine in Brussels on 18 May, 1535.</note> hoc enim ex litteris
                    caesaris ad principem meum iamdiu audivimus. Caesar transmittet in Italia,
                    classis paratur. <persName>Princeps Auria</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.5">Andrea Doria.</note> cum XV triremibus brevi profecturus est
                        <placeName>Baradino</placeName>, nam caesare ita iubente.
                        <persName>Pontifex</persName> in Gallicas partes inclinat, sed parum de eo
                    timendum est, non enim hiscere audebit. Quae de
                        <persName>Aenobarbo</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Hayreddin
                        Barbarossa Pasha.</note> nuper intelleximus, item urbana nova et Hispanica,
                        <persName>dux</persName> serenissimae reginae uberrime scribit. Ensem
                        Italicum<note type="critic" xml:id="note.7">See Ep.
                            528.<ref>olahus.tei.15350209_1</ref></note> habebis brevi affabre
                    factum. Haec scripsi temporibus exclusus, tu veniam mihi dabis, si longiori
                    epistola non utar. Vale et <persName>Scepperum</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.8">Cornelis de Schepper.</note> saluta meo nomine. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XI. Martii anno MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
